  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CA Leasing Facility</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFC plans to create a Central Asia Leasing Facility (the facility or the company) to expand financing options for small- and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) and help them expand their operations, as well as to introduce competition in the financial sector.  The facility will on-lend to selected local financial institutions  banks, leasing companies and NGOs  to write leases in Kazakhstan, Kyrgyz Republic, Uzbekistan and later, Tajikistan.  Selection of participating financial institutions will be based on criteria such as:  track record of financial soundness, clear corporate governance and transparency standards, and demonstrated commitment to leasing and to the SME sector.  The facility will be supported by a donor-funded technical assistance program to address capacity and operational needs of local financial institutions.</narrative>
  </description>
